Validate Power: d2.2_m2rc

Kristin Porter, Zarni Htet, Kristen Hunter

August 10, 2021

Design: Cluster RCT, with 2 levels, and randomization done at level 2 (school level).

Models: random treatment effects.

Default parameters:

  • M = 3
  • J = 60
  • rho: \(\rho\) = 0.5
  • ATE ES = 0.125, 0.125, 0.125
  • R2: \(R^2_1\) = 0.1, 0.1, 0.1, \(R^2_2\) = 0.1, 0.1, 0.1
  • ICC: \(\text{ICC}_2\) = 0.1, 0.1, 0.1

Assumptions

  • Two-level design: \(\text{ICC}_3 = 0\), \(\omega_3 = 0\), \(K = 1\)
  • Constant treatment effects: \(\omega_2 = 0\)

Power Validation

Base case

Varying school size

\(\bar{n}\) = 100

\(\bar{n}\) = 75

Varying R2

\(R^2_1 =\) 0.6, 0.6, 0.6

\(R^2_2 =\) 0.6, 0.6, 0.6

\(R^2_1 =\) 0, 0, 0 \(R^2_2 =\) 0, 0, 0

Varying rho

\(\rho =\) 0.2

\(\rho =\) 0.8

Varying true positives

ATE (ES) = 0.125, 0, 0

Varying ICC

\(\text{ICC}_2\) = 0.7, 0.7, 0.7

\(\text{ICC}_2\) = 0, 0, 0

Kappa

\(\kappa\) = 0.4
